+   - mild / maximal-lifespan critical-space evolutions,
+   - and any mixed bridge architecture if the repository actually supports one.
+2. What theorem-level contradiction endpoints or cash-out lines are locally
+   supported for those frameworks?
+   Examples: endpoint regularity exclusion, backward-uniqueness-style rigidity,
+   Liouville / ancient-solution exclusion, epsilon-regularity contradiction, or
+   another exact line explicitly present in the local record.
+3. What temporal architecture does each serious setup suggest for a later
+   critical object?
+   Distinguish clearly between forward maximal-lifespan, ancient solution,
+   normalized near blowup time, or another explicit package.
+4. What exact bridge, if any, connects each framework candidate back to the
+   inherited suitable-weak / local-energy floor?
+   Say plainly if the local record does not support that bridge.
+5. What prior-art or overlap warnings already exist locally for each setup?
+6. What burden categories and progress-currency candidates are actually
+   supported by the local record for this chain?
+
+Please prefer source packets that let later explorers cite exact local files
+for framework, endpoint, temporal architecture, bridge, burden-ledger, and
+progress-currency claims. If the record suggests that no single framework can
+carry extraction, critical-object packaging, and later rigidity on one ledger,
+say so explicitly and identify the cleanest source support.
