 # Strategizer Reasoning
 
-The strategizer will append its execution reasoning here.
+## 2026-03-31 Initial Read
+
+- `GOAL.md` freezes Chain Step 1 of the new run-005 compactness-rigidity
+  branch: choose one solution framework, one theorem endpoint, one temporal
+  architecture, one bridge to the inherited suitable-weak / LEI floor, one
+  burden ledger, and one progress currency before any host-space ranking.
+- `step-007/RESULTS.md` killed the earlier branch because every host-space
+  candidate drifted across incompatible architectures and diffuse missing
+  stacks. That negative result is still active evidence here: Step 8 cannot
+  silently revive the old branch by mixing frameworks midstream.
+- `controller/decisions/decision-011.md` explicitly says the old active chain
+  should not proceed and forbids rescuing it by a silent architecture change.
+  The current step therefore has to earn a fresh one-ledger setup or produce a
+  setup-stage obstruction.
+- `run-005/winning-chain.md` and `run-005/final-decider.md` narrow the task:
+  freeze the framework and theorem endpoint first, keep burden columns
+  separated, count stacked theorem debt as decisive failure, and measure later
+  claims in one explicit progress currency.
+
+## Receptionist Query Rationale
+
+- A receptionist pass is required before new explorations.
+- The key question is no longer host-space ranking. It is whether the local
+  corpus supports one coherent setup menu of frameworks and contradiction
+  endpoints, together with concrete temporal packaging and a non-symbolic
+  bridge to the inherited suitable-weak / local-energy floor.
+- The receptionist should return exact source packets for:
+  candidate frameworks still live after `step-007` and `run-005`,
+  theorem-level endpoints or contradiction lines,
+  temporal-architecture evidence,
+  LEI / suitable-weak bridge evidence,
+  prior-art / overlap warnings,
+  burden-ledger categories,
+  and plausible progress currencies.
+
+## 2026-03-31 Post-Receptionist Direction
+
+- The receptionist result confirms a very narrow serious menu:
+  the inherited suitable-weak / Leray-Hopf plus LEI floor is the only fully
+  supported architecture, `L^3` and `\dot H^{1/2}` remain diffuse-package
+  candidates, `BMO^{-1}` stays excluded, and no mixed bridge architecture is
+  locally supported.
+- That is strong evidence for a setup obstruction, but the step still needs a
+  disciplined source-backed freeze:
+  one exploration should collapse the framework-and-endpoint menu and one
+  exploration should test whether any single one-ledger setup survives.
+- Exploration 001 will freeze the serious menu:
+  distinguish true framework candidates from mere host-space language,
+  identify the theorem-level endpoint families actually supported locally,
+  and state what the inherited suitable-weak / LEI floor fixes.
+- Exploration 002 will then test one-ledger coherence:
+  temporal architecture,
+  exact bridge requirements,
